BMW Group’s Augmented Vision goggles will go on show at the Auto Shanghai show . 
  The goggles can project navigation information onto the road . 
  It can also show speed limits and point out local landmarks . 
  BMW Group‘s answer to Google Glass is designed to let drivers of its Mini model see pop-up virtual displays for maps and other features . 
  The Elvis-style glasses can also be worn out of the car . 
  The glasses are connected to a smartphone and generate ‘screens’ showing information only the driver can see . 
 